title: For Sale:   WINCHESTER 1876 DELUXE HIGH COND.
postcontent: Winchester Model 1876 Deluxe sporting rifle chambered in the 40-60 caliber. This rifle, serial #530** was manufactured in 1886, has six special order features and comes with a letter taken from the factory ledgers housed at the Cody Firearms Museum showing its original configuration. With the Model 1876 already having a low production of 63,871 guns, there were only 9,132 rifles manufactured in the 40-60. The 40-60 caliber had the fewest number of Deluxe guns made with only 268. The 50-95 Express rifles had the lowest production numbers of 3,281, but had 539 Deluxe models manufactured. The 45-75 had rifles, with 802 Deluxe guns and the 45-60 had 24,176 rifles with 530 being Deluxe models. The other extremely rare features are that only a total of 76 rifles were manufactured with a 28" half octagon/half round barrel (which many of those would have had full magazines). stamped on the lower left tang of the receiver and on the inlet of the stock. see pics
